other_tests.findings: Streaky opacities in the bilateral lung bases compatible with minimal bibasilar atelectasis. The liver enhances homogeneously without evidence of concerning focal lesion. There is a tubular, blind-ending structure in the right lower quadrant with mildly thickened, enhancing walls, and equivocal findings for early or mild appendicitis. A peripherally enhancing, 1.8 cm hypodensity compatible with a corpus luteal cyst in the right adnexa.
